ðŸ“… Day 1 â€“ Machine Learning Fundamentals
Concepts Covered

What Machine Learning is:
Learning patterns from historical data to make predictions on new data.

Why Machine Learning is needed:
Rule-based systems fail when:

Relationships are non-linear

Data volume is large

Rules are dynamic or unknown

Types of Machine Learning:

Supervised Learning: Labeled data (used in this project)

Unsupervised Learning: Pattern discovery

Reinforcement Learning: Reward-based learning

Machine Learning Workflow:

Problem Definition
